# Vercel Environment Variables for AutoDealGenie Frontend
# Add these in your Vercel dashboard: Settings → Environment Variables

# ===========================
# REQUIRED VARIABLES
# ===========================

# Backend API URL - Update this after deploying backend to Render
# Development Environment (set for "dev" branch)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-app-backend-dev.onrender.com

# Production Environment (set for "main" branch)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-app-backend-prod.onrender.com

# API Version (same for all environments)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_VERSION=v1

# Node Environment (automatically set by Vercel)
# NODE_ENV=production

# ===========================
# OPTIONAL VARIABLES
# ===========================

# Mock Services (for testing without backend)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_USE_MOCK=false

# ===========================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ===========================
# 
# 1. Deploy to Vercel:
#    a. Go to https://vercel.com and sign in with GitHub
#    b. Click "Add New" → "Project"
#    c. Import your GitHub repository
#    d. Configure the project:
#       - Framework Preset: Next.js
#       - Root Directory: frontend
#       - Build Command: npm run build
#       - Output Directory: .next
#       - Install Command: npm install
#
# 2. Set up environment variables:
#    a. Go to Project Settings → Environment Variables
#    b. Add NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL:
#       - For "dev" branch: https://autodealgenie-backend-dev.onrender.com
#       - For "main" branch: https://autodealgenie-backend-prod.onrender.com
#    c. Add NEXT_PUBLIC_API_VERSION: v1
#
# 3. Configure deployment branches:
#    a. Go to Settings → Git
#    b. Set Production Branch: main
#    c. Enable automatic deployments for:
#       - main branch → Production
#       - dev branch → Preview (development environment)
#
# 4. Update backend CORS:
#    After deploying, update your Render backend's BACKEND_CORS_ORIGINS
#    to include your Vercel URLs:
#    - Development: https://<your-app>-<hash>-<team>.vercel.app
#    - Production: https://<your-app>.vercel.app
#
# 5. Custom Domain (Optional):
#    a. Go to Settings → Domains
#    b. Add your custom domain
#    c. Update DNS records as instructed
#    d. Update backend CORS to include custom domain
#
# ===========================
# VERCEL-SPECIFIC FEATURES
# ===========================
#
# Automatic Preview Deployments:
# - Every push to non-production branches creates a preview deployment
# - Each preview gets a unique URL
# - Perfect for testing before merging to main
#
# Environment Variables per Branch:
# - Set different values for Production, Preview, and Development
# - Production: main branch
# - Preview: dev branch and all other branches
# - Development: Local development
#
# Edge Functions:
# - Vercel automatically optimizes Next.js for edge deployment
# - API routes run on serverless functions
# - Static pages served from CDN
#
# Performance:
# - Automatic image optimization
# - Automatic font optimization
# - Built-in CDN for static assets
# - Brotli compression
#
# ===========================
# NOTES
# ===========================
# - Vercel free tier includes:
#   - Unlimited deployments
#   - 100GB bandwidth/month
#   - 100 serverless function invocations/day
#   - Automatic HTTPS
#   - Preview deployments for all branches
#
# - Environment variables prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are:
#   - Embedded in the frontend bundle at build time
#   - Accessible in browser code
#   - Cannot be changed without rebuilding
#
# - Vercel automatically sets:
#   - VERCEL=1
#   - VERCEL_ENV (production, preview, or development)
#   - VERCEL_URL (deployment URL)
#   - VERCEL_GIT_COMMIT_SHA
#   - VERCEL_GIT_COMMIT_REF (branch name)
#
# - To test backend connection:
#   - Check browser console for API errors
#   - Verify CORS settings in backend
#   - Ensure backend is not spun down (Render free tier)
#   - Check that backend URL is correct (no trailing slash)
